Change Your Chat Status

Change your Chat status to control when youâ€™re available to receive new and transferred chats.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance Editions and in Developer Edition orgs that were created after June 14, 2012
Available in: Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To chat with visitors in the Salesforce console: Chat is enabled, set up, and included in a Salesforce console app

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026.

In Chat, you can set your online status to online, away, or offline. When you exit Chat, your status automatically changes to offline and any active chat sessions end.

Click the Chat footer or Omni-Channel window to open the chat monitor.
Click the drop-down arrow in the upper right corner of the chat monitor to view your status options.
Select your status.

Chat Statuses
Chat statuses define how you can interact with customers while you're online, away, or offline.
